<div id="home">

<img src="/assets/me_and_maxwell.jpg" alt="Self portrait with canned coffee" title="Me and Maxwell" style="float: left; margin-right: 30px;"><p class="drop-cap">There are already pages about <a href="/projects/index.html">my work</a> and <a href="/contact/index.html">contacting me</a>. This is more about me (me, me).</p>

<p>The notable points, so far:</p>

<ul>
<li><p>Born and raised in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baldwinsville">Baldwinsville, NY</a>, a suburb of Syracuse (though technically <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lysander,_New_York">Lysander</a>, if you're taking a census).</p></li>
<li><p>Educated (as best they could try) by the <a href="http://buffalo.edu">University at Buffalo</a>, where I predominantly wrote for <a href="http://ubspectrum.com"><em>The Spectrum</em></a>.</p></li>
<li><p>Worked as something of a long-term intern/temp at <a href="http://buffalonews.com"><em>The Buffalo News</em></a>, then the <a href="http://sanduskyregister.com"><em>Sandusky Register</em></a>, then the <a href="http://niagara-gazette.com"><em>Niagara Gazette</em></a> and its affiliated local papers.</p></li>
<li><p>I made the jump from print to web when <a href="http://ginatrapani.org">Gina Trapani</a> responded to my email and hired me on at <a href="http://lifehacker.com"><em>Lifehacker</em></a>.</p></li>
<li><p>After more than 3 years and <a href="http://lifehacker.com/5797054/five-lists-of-five-things-i-learned-at-lifehacker">5,883 posts</a>, I left Lifehacker to strike out on my own. I'm now writing for <a href="http://kevinpurdy.contently.com/">quite a few different publications</a>.</li>
</ul>

<img src="/assets/writing_tedxbuffalo_intro.jpg" style="float: right; margin-left: 30px;"/>

<p>I have a <a href="http://elizabethfoxsolomon.com">wonderful wife</a>, a <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/purdman1/tags/howard/">dog named Howard</a>, two cats (Cork and Apricot), and a m√©nagerie of friends and side projects to keep me busy.</p>

<p>If you're wondering what this site is made out of, <a href="/colophon.md">check the colophon</a>.</p>

<p>Wherever you go, there you are.</p>
</div>
